1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,218
Dr. Khalifa: ... (unintelligible)

2
00:00:04,643 --> 00:00:11,599
Dr. Khalifa: So, if I (unintelligible), you have the choice, I mean, to agree with it or disagree with it.

3
00:00:12,543 --> 00:00:17,956
And when you express an opinion, you may convince me of changing my opinion, or I may choose not to take your opinion.

4
00:00:17,956 --> 00:00:26,930
So, the purpose of reading Al-Fãtehah is for Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala to guide us to see the truth and to remain as brothers, whether the difference between us or not.

5
00:00:26,930 --> 00:00:31,024
And I'm hoping that the people who hate me
this morning will love me at the end of their (unintelligible)

6
00:00:31,024 --> 00:00:33,856
Because I love them (unintelligible). I'm happy.

7
00:00:33,856 --> 00:00:34,996
I know you're sincere.

8
00:00:34,996 --> 00:00:39,232
And I know that most people who go to the
mosque or church will break God's law.

9
00:00:40,515 --> 00:00:43,787
We're all Muslims, and I love you for it.

10
00:00:44,070 --> 00:00:46,563
You are very enthusiastic, and I love you
for it.

11
00:00:47,271 --> 00:00:49,095
And I hope at the end, we will be brothers.

12
00:00:49,410 --> 00:00:52,794
I may have a different opinion than you. You
may have a different opinion than mine.

13
00:00:54,083 --> 00:00:57,842
But I'm convinced, and I really mean it,
that you are sincere people.

14
00:00:58,146 --> 00:01:03,999
And I love you are here, and not in a nightclub,
or watching a dancer, or breaking God's law in any way.

15
00:01:04,583 --> 00:01:07,065
You'll never break God's law. I know that you follow the Quran.

16
00:01:07,882 --> 00:01:11,899
So, and I grew up in the same conditions as you.

17
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:14,836
I passed through the same stages that you're passing through.

18
00:01:15,584 --> 00:01:19,615
And we change, people change, because we learn,
otherwise there is no use.

19
00:01:19,804 --> 00:01:23,931
Every day that we don't learn something, and
we change a little bit, is not worth living.

20
00:01:25,536 --> 00:01:31,447
So, we're going to read Al-Fãtehah now, and we sincerely turn to Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala to guide us to the truth.

21
00:01:31,759 --> 00:01:34,113
Guide me to the truth, and guide you to the
truth.

22
00:01:34,820 --> 00:01:37,021
And we'll be sincere, IN SHAA ALLAH, in reciting Al-Fãtehah.

23
00:01:37,021 --> 00:01:39,493
For only Quran says
Eyyaka Na’abudu Wa Eyyaka Nasta’aeen (1:5)

24
00:01:40,484 --> 00:01:41,351
Al-Fãtehah

25
00:01:41,823 --> 00:02:00,609
Bism Allah Arrahman Arraheem (1:1)
Al hamdu Lillahi Rabbil ‘Alameen (1:2)
Arrahman Arraheem (1:3)
Maliki Yawm Eddeen (1:4)
Eyyaka Na’abudu Wa Eyyaka Nasta’aeen (1:5)
Ehdina Al-Serata Al-Mustaqeem (1:6)
Serata Al-Lazeena An’amta ‘Alayhim Ghayri Al-Maghdoobi ‘Alayhim Wa Laddaalleen (1:7)

26
00:02:02,167 --> 00:02:03,837
Bism Allah Arrahman Arraheem

27
00:02:05,536 --> 00:02:06,781
Alhamdu Lillah

28
00:02:08,781 --> 00:02:11,536
In the name of God, Most Gracious, Most Merciful

29
00:02:11,536 --> 00:02:12,922
Praise be to God.

30
00:02:13,205 --> 00:02:15,205
Wa Ash-hadu Alla Elaha Ella Allah.

31
00:02:15,488 --> 00:02:18,904
And I bear witness that there is no
god except the One God.

32
00:02:18,904 --> 00:02:20,574
Wahdahu La Shareeka Lah

33
00:02:20,574 --> 00:02:22,810
He alone is God. He has no partners.

34
00:02:23,612 --> 00:02:27,311
Our topic this morning is, why...

35
00:02:28,585 --> 00:02:31,718
This is Canada, North America, the folks say anything they want.

36
00:02:33,370 --> 00:02:36,739
This is not Egypt or Iraq, or any other place.

37
00:02:36,739 --> 00:02:37,937
They say anything they want.

38
00:02:42,752 --> 00:02:46,781
The topic this morning is (unintelligible) or the reason why we are here.

39
00:02:47,159 --> 00:02:49,159
"Why are we here? What is our objective?"

40
00:02:49,537 --> 00:02:58,569
Are we here to go to school and get a degree, and make a lot of money, and build a big house, and have a beautiful wife, and a lot of children?

41
00:02:59,661 --> 00:03:04,606
Are we here for this, to make a lot of money, and have a nice home, be respectful to society?

42
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,190
What are we here for?

43
00:03:09,022 --> 00:03:15,793
The teacher, Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala,
in the Quran, teaches us, tell us why we are here.

44
00:03:15,995 --> 00:03:20,334
In Sura Al-Dhãreyãt, number 51, Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala says,

45
00:03:20,334 --> 00:03:22,806
(51:56) وَمَا خَلَقْتُ ٱلْجِنَّ وَٱلْإِنسَ إِلَّا لِيَعْبُدُونِ

46
00:03:23,420 --> 00:03:24,618
These are two negatives.

47
00:03:24,854 --> 00:03:30,252
[51:56]  I did not create the humans and the jinns except to worship Me alone.

48
00:03:30,252 --> 00:03:31,775
That's what Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala said.

49
00:03:31,775 --> 00:03:34,801
So, that is the purpose of, of us being here.

50
00:03:35,603 --> 00:03:41,054
But what we forget to remember is that we
have an archenemy.

51
00:03:41,847 --> 00:03:49,106
You and I have a common enemy that we must
band together against, instead of fighting with each other.

52
00:03:49,106 --> 00:03:54,386
And this archenemy, that is your enemy and
my enemy, is called Iblis (Satan).

53
00:03:54,699 --> 00:03:56,605
He swore by God's Majesty.

54
00:03:56,888 --> 00:03:59,171
(38:82) فَبِعِزَّتِكَ لَأُغْوِيَنَّهُمْ أَجْمَعِينَ

55
00:03:59,596 --> 00:04:02,823
"I swear by Your Majesty, I will deceive them
all."

56
00:04:03,059 --> 00:04:05,059
(38:83) إِلَّا عِبَادَكَ مِنْهُمُ ٱلْمُخْلَصِينَ

57
00:04:05,339 --> 00:04:12,761
The only people who can escape the grip of Iblis (Satan) are the people who are totally devoted Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala.

58
00:04:12,761 --> 00:04:14,761
(38:83) إِلَّا عِبَادَكَ مِنْهُمُ ٱلْمُخْلَصِينَ

59
00:04:16,169 --> 00:04:21,327
Iblis swore that he will come from in front
of us, from behind us, from our right and our left.

60
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:29,369
لَـَٔاتِيَنَّهُم مِّنۢ بَيْنِ أَيْدِيهِمْ وَمِنْ خَلْفِهِمْ وَعَنْ أَيْمَـٰنِهِمْ وَعَن
(7:17) شَمَآئِلِهِمْ ۖ وَلَا تَجِدُ أَكْثَرَهُمْ شَـٰكِرِينَ

61
00:04:30,342 --> 00:04:34,779
[7:17]  "... You will find that most of them are unappreciative."

62
00:04:34,779 --> 00:04:35,646
of You.

63
00:04:40,885 --> 00:04:47,180
Satan (Iblis), unfortunately, succeeded
to a great extent.

64
00:04:47,505 --> 00:04:50,934
And this is recorded in the Quran, and we
see it in life.

65
00:04:52,350 --> 00:04:57,878
Of all the followers of Jesus Christ, how many billions follow him as he really wants to be followed?

66
00:04:58,912 --> 00:05:02,074
How many Christians believe that Jesus is
a messenger of God?

67
00:05:02,546 --> 00:05:06,045
And how many believe that he's son of God, or God, or part of the Trinity?

68
00:05:07,225 --> 00:05:10,799
How many of them love Jesus, of the Christians?

69
00:05:11,145 --> 00:05:12,991
This is what Iblis did to them.

70
00:05:14,218 --> 00:05:22,637
Iblis convinced them that they love Jesus so much that he must be greater than a human being and a messenger of God.

71
00:05:25,186 --> 00:05:29,121
Satan came to them from their right, from
their left, from their front, from their back.

72
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,528
And you see the results.

73
00:05:31,764 --> 00:05:34,850
You and I agree on the results of what happened
to the Christians.

74
00:05:35,605 --> 00:05:38,077
You and I agree on what happened to the Jews.

75
00:05:38,643 --> 00:05:41,257
First, he made them disrespect their prophets.

76
00:05:41,493 --> 00:05:43,068
They killed their prophets.

77
00:05:43,304 --> 00:05:45,068
They have no respect for Moses.

78
00:05:45,446 --> 00:05:50,278
They have no respect for any of the prophets. And historically, as recorded in the Quran, the Jews killed their prophets.

79
00:05:50,703 --> 00:05:52,703
They have absolutely no respect for them.

80
00:05:53,081 --> 00:05:59,376
But Satan, Iblis, turned around and he made
them reverence and worship their scholars.

81
00:05:59,801 --> 00:06:03,500
(9:31) ٱتَّخَذُوٓا۟ أَحْبَارَهُمْ وَرُهْبَـٰنَهُمْ أَرْبَابًۭا مِّن دُونِ ٱللَّهِ

82
00:06:03,860 --> 00:06:07,465
They set up their rabbis and their priests
as gods beside God.

83
00:06:07,701 --> 00:06:08,474
How?

84
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:13,746
The Ahbar (أَحْبَار) and the Rohban (رُهْبَـٰنَ),

85
00:06:13,746 --> 00:06:18,106
the rabbis and the priests wrote
for them the Talmud,

86
00:06:18,106 --> 00:06:24,684
which is divided into two parts, Mishnah which means Hadith and Gemarrah which means Sunna. This is the Talmud.

87
00:06:24,684 --> 00:06:27,534
(unintelligible)

88
00:06:28,242 --> 00:06:34,207
The Talmud is now followed by the Jews, not
the Torah. They do not follow the Torah. They follow the Talmud.

89
00:06:35,104 --> 00:06:37,670
Iblis succeeded with the Jews and misled them.

90
00:06:38,048 --> 00:06:41,134
(9:31) ٱتَّخَذُوٓا۟ أَحْبَارَهُمْ وَرُهْبَـٰنَهُمْ أَرْبَابًۭا مِّن دُونِ ٱللَّهِ

91
00:06:41,512 --> 00:06:47,005
They, they set up their religious scholars as gods
besides God.

92
00:06:49,270 --> 00:06:52,214
And they take the words of God, the Torah.

93
00:06:52,828 --> 00:06:57,282
With the Christians, Satan misled them by
the millions.

94
00:06:58,179 --> 00:07:02,869
I mean, you can stand here and say "are those millions
upon millions of Christians wrong and you are right?"

95
00:07:03,105 --> 00:07:04,208
You can say that.

96
00:07:04,444 --> 00:07:05,642
And of course, they are wrong.

97
00:07:05,925 --> 00:07:07,311
And it's because of Iblis.

98
00:07:07,641 --> 00:07:10,538
And because idol worship is very subtle.

99
00:07:11,812 --> 00:07:13,293
أَخْفَى مِنْ دَبِيبِ النَّمْلِ

100
00:07:13,293 --> 00:07:14,160
Shirk

101
00:07:14,585 --> 00:07:17,529
If there's an ant crawling in there, you
will not see it.

102
00:07:17,529 --> 00:07:24,201
And if you hold an idol worship, if I hold
an idol worship, we will not see it, unless we resort to the Quran.

103
00:07:24,201 --> 00:07:29,652
Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala is The Savior who
gives us criteria to detect our idol worship.

104
00:07:31,699 --> 00:07:41,401
The Quran teaches us that the Shirk is so hidden, idol worship is so hidden, that you and I swear, by God, that we are not idol worshipers.

105
00:07:42,272 --> 00:07:50,000
And until the
Day of Judgment, some people will swear by God,

106
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:53,652
face to face, on the Day of Judgment,
that they are not idol worshipers.

107
00:07:54,030 --> 00:07:55,841
(6:22) وَيَوْمَ نَحْشُرُهُمْ جَمِيعًۭا

108
00:07:55,841 --> 00:07:57,841
On the Day, we gather them all.

109
00:07:57,841 --> 00:08:02,673
(6:22) ثُمَّ نَقُولُ لِلَّذِينَ أَشْرَكُوٓا۟ أَيْنَ شُرَكَآؤُكُمُ ٱلَّذِينَ كُنتُمْ تَزْعُمُونَ

110
00:08:02,673 --> 00:08:06,912
Then, we say to the idol worshipers, where are your idols now to help you?

111
00:08:07,195 --> 00:08:12,357
(6:23) ثُمَّ لَمْ تَكُن فِتْنَتُهُمْ إِلَّآ أَن قَالُوا۟ وَٱللَّهِ رَبِّنَا مَا كُنَّا مُشْرِكِينَ

112
00:08:12,876 --> 00:08:17,519
Their only answer would be "we swear by God,
our Lord, we were not idol worshipers."

113
00:08:18,179 --> 00:08:20,462
(6:24) ٱنظُرْ كَيْفَ كَذَبُوا۟ عَلَىٰٓ أَنفُسِهِمْ

114
00:08:21,170 --> 00:08:25,483
I mean, I can lie to somebody, I can lie to
other people, but lying to myself!?

115
00:08:26,710 --> 00:08:28,285
They lied to themselves.

116
00:08:28,899 --> 00:08:31,701
They told themselves "I am not an idol worshiper."

117
00:08:31,937 --> 00:08:36,769
"I swear by God, my Lord, that I am not an
idol worshiper."

118
00:08:37,005 --> 00:08:41,837
And on the Day of Judgment, face to face with
Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala, they will swear,

119
00:08:41,837 --> 00:08:44,734
"by God, our Lord, we are not idol worshipers."

120
00:08:46,734 --> 00:08:53,784
We learn in Sura Al-Nahl, Sura 16, verse
22, that what we say with our mouths does not mean a thing.

121
00:08:54,350 --> 00:09:00,267
I can say "I believe in God, I believe in the
Hereafter", but my heart inside may deny that.

122
00:09:00,550 --> 00:09:02,172
(16:22) إِلَـٰهُكُمْ إِلَـٰهٌۭ وَٰحِدٌۭ ۚ

123
00:09:02,408 --> 00:09:04,125
[2:163]  Your god is one god

124
00:09:04,408 --> 00:09:07,730
(16:22) فَٱلَّذِينَ لَا يُؤْمِنُونَ بِٱلْـَٔاخِرَةِ قُلُوبُهُم مُّنكِرَةٌۭ

125
00:09:08,013 --> 00:09:13,553
Those who do not believe in the Hereafter, their hearts inside are denying what they say with their mouths.

126
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:15,931
(unintelligible)

127
00:09:18,356 --> 00:09:21,772
Well, and how do we know then that we are not
idol worshipers?

128
00:09:21,772 --> 00:09:24,008
How do I know that I'm not an idol worshiper?

129
00:09:24,952 --> 00:09:31,719
If it is a fact, and it is a fact because it is mentioned in Quran, that there are people, on the Day of Judgment, who swear

130
00:09:31,719 --> 00:09:33,719
(6:23) وَٱللَّهِ رَبِّنَا مَا كُنَّا مُشْرِكِينَ

131
00:09:34,348 --> 00:09:37,747
How do I know that
I am not one of those people?

132
00:09:40,815 --> 00:09:46,030
There's one way to find out, and that is
to wait until the Day of Judgment and then find out.

133
00:09:47,125 --> 00:09:48,787
I go in that group and I say,

134
00:09:48,787 --> 00:09:50,787
وَٱللَّهِ رَبِّنَا مَا كُنت مُشْرِك

135
00:09:51,619 --> 00:09:55,019
And then, I find out that I was idol worshiper
and I was unaware.

136
00:09:55,019 --> 00:09:59,425
This is one way of finding out, and you will
agree with me that it is not the right way.

137
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:03,918
The other right way, the other way, is to
find out now.

138
00:10:05,189 --> 00:10:11,036
You and I want to find out if we are worshipping
our Creator, who created us or not.

139
00:10:11,036 --> 00:10:15,821
(30:40) ٱللَّهُ ٱلَّذِى خَلَقَكُمْ ثُمَّ رَزَقَكُمْ ثُمَّ يُمِيتُكُمْ ثُمَّ يُحْيِيكُمْ

140
00:10:15,821 --> 00:10:17,585
[30:40]  GOD is the One who created you. ...

141
00:10:17,585 --> 00:10:24,635
God is the One provided for you. God is the One who
will terminate your life. God is the One who resurrects you.

142
00:10:25,060 --> 00:10:32,724
So, you and I must find out whether we are
worshipping our Creator, our Provider, or not.

143
00:10:33,526 --> 00:10:39,727
The message of Quran states that it is Allah
alone. This is the key that we must worship.

144
00:10:40,341 --> 00:10:49,421
That Allah alone will not need any help or assistance or a servant or a king or anything with Him, that we accept Allah alone by Himself.

145
00:10:51,686 --> 00:10:53,686
What are the criteria? How do we find out?

146
00:10:53,686 --> 00:10:58,093
The intelligent, first, if I am intelligent,
I will put myself on trial.

147
00:10:58,093 --> 00:11:01,839
I will say "Rashad Khalifa, you are an idol
worshipper, but you don't know."

148
00:11:03,028 --> 00:11:11,123
And I want to prove very hard that I am not an idol worshipper, but first I must accuse myself of being an idol worshipper.

149
00:11:11,123 --> 00:11:13,899
And you come to me and say "Rashad Khalifa,
you're an idol worshipper."

150
00:11:13,899 --> 00:11:18,478
If I am smart, I will say "wait a minute,
maybe I am."

151
00:11:19,722 --> 00:11:24,874
Let us see, let us prove that I am an idol
worshipper, until I fail.

152
00:11:25,870 --> 00:11:33,884
I must, actually, set out to prove that I am an idol worshipper, and not be convinced until I fail to prove that I am an idol worshipper.

153
00:11:34,262 --> 00:11:36,262
I have to put myself on trial.

154
00:11:36,734 --> 00:11:39,395
We must hold ourselves accountable here.

155
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:46,295
And we have the book that will teach us how
to find out.

156
00:11:47,853 --> 00:11:52,260
There are criteria in the Quran. This is why
one of the names of the Quran is Al-Furqãn.

157
00:11:53,393 --> 00:11:58,461
It provides criteria to tell us "am I an idol
worshipper or not?"

158
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,528
I have to assume that I am.

159
00:12:01,528 --> 00:12:02,236
(unintelligible)

160
00:12:02,802 --> 00:12:07,303
Because we are free in this world to say anything.
We are free to believe in anything.

161
00:12:07,917 --> 00:12:12,843
And this is our chance to correct any error or any
mistake that you may fall in.

162
00:12:14,843 --> 00:12:20,000
The first criterion, we find in Sura Al-Zumer.

163
00:12:21,794 --> 00:12:23,794
Sura 39, verse 45.

164
00:12:24,266 --> 00:12:26,266
And here's the criterion, it says,

165
00:12:26,738 --> 00:12:28,738
وَإِذَا ذُكِرَ ٱللَّهُ وَحْدَهُ

166
00:12:29,635 --> 00:12:32,390
When God alone is mentioned,

167
00:12:32,626 --> 00:12:35,617
ٱشْمَأَزَّتْ قُلُوبُ ٱلَّذِينَ لَا يُؤْمِنُونَ بِٱلْـَٔاخِرَةِ

168
00:12:36,372 --> 00:12:40,826
The heart of those who do not believe in the Hereafter... remember
the verse?

169
00:12:41,062 --> 00:12:42,732
(16:22) ٱلَّذِينَ لَا يُؤْمِنُونَ ... قُلُوبُهُم مُّنكِرَةٌۭ

170
00:12:42,732 --> 00:12:44,024
Their hearts are denying.

171
00:12:44,307 --> 00:12:48,289
The hearts of those who do not believe in the Hereafter become upset. They become upset.

172
00:12:48,572 --> 00:12:50,000
وَإِذَا ذُكِرَ ٱللَّهُ وَحْدَهُ

173
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,330
When God alone is mentioned, they become upset.

174
00:12:52,330 --> 00:12:58,011
So, I have to ask myself "Rashad Khalifa, you're an idol worshipper", and I want to apply this criterion to you.

175
